dainty /ˈdeɪntɪ/

(daintier,daintiest) 

1. ADJ If you describe a movement, person, or object as dainty , you mean that they are small, delicate, and pretty. 娇小漂亮的 

例： The girls were dainty and feminine. 这些女子们娇美而又温柔。 

2. daintily ADV 娇小漂亮地 

例： She walked daintily down the steps. 她优雅轻盈地走下台阶。

